.TH "uart_parse_earlycon" 9 "uart_parse_earlycon" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
uart_parse_earlycon \- Parse earlycon options
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" uart_parse_earlycon
.BI "(char *p "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *iotype "  ","
.BI "resource_size_t *addr "  ","
.BI "char **options "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "p" 12
ptr to 2nd field (ie., just beyond '<name>,')
.IP "iotype" 12
ptr for decoded iotype (out)
.IP "addr" 12
ptr for decoded mapbase/iobase (out)
.IP "options" 12
ptr for <options> field; NULL if not present (out)

Decodes earlycon kernel command line parameters of the form
earlycon=<name>,io|mmio|mmio16|mmio32|mmio32be|mmio32native,<addr>,<options>
console=<name>,io|mmio|mmio16|mmio32|mmio32be|mmio32native,<addr>,<options>

The optional form

earlycon=<name>,0x<addr>,<options>
console=<name>,0x<addr>,<options>

is also accepted; the returned \fIiotype\fP will be UPIO_MEM.

Returns 0 on success or -EINVAL on failure
